The paper deals with graph querying, which is a problem commonly studied in the database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of contextual information and relationships in the query suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The proposed CGQ-Tree index and search algorithm indicate a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). Finally, the scalability of the approach suggests a possible fit with the systems and networking (cs.SI) sub-category.
